{
  "texts": [
    "We show L nn is noise tolerant as follows (we recall the definitions of different noise rates can be found in Section III-B):Theorem 2.",
    "In a multi-class classification problem, any normalized negative loss function L nn is noise tolerant under symmetric label noise, if noise rate η < K-1 K. Theorem 3.",
    "In a multi-class classification problem, supposeL nn satisfies 0 ≤ L nn (f (x), k) ≤ 1, ∀k ∈ {1, • • •, K}.",
    "If R(f *) = 0,then, any normalized negative loss function L nn is noise tolerant under asymmetric label noise when noise rate η yk < 1 -η y.Detailed proofs are provided in Appendix B. Theorems 2 and 3 show that under some mild assumptions, our proposed NNLFs are noise tolerant, which means they are robust to noise.3) ANL is robust to noise: Similar to APL, we can show that our ANL is also robust to label noise.",
    "∀α, β, the combination L ANL = αL norm + βL nn is noise tolerant under both symmetric and asymmetric label noise.The proofs are outlined in Appendix B. Theorem 4 shows that the combination of normalized loss functions and our NNLFs are robust to noise."
  ]
